              "      <td>You are a helpful mental health counselling assistant, please answer the mental health questions based on the patient's description. \\nThe assistant gives helpful, comprehensive, and appropriate answers to the user's questions.</td>\n",
              "      <td>Thank you for your advice, counselor. I feel a bit more hopeful now that I have some concrete strategies to manage my siblings' demands and prioritize my mom's care. I'll start by setting specific times for responding to their requests and delegating tasks to others. I'll also look into local support groups and resources for caregivers. I know it won't be easy, but I'm determined to make things work for both my mom and me.</td>\n",
              "      <td>I'm glad to hear that you feel more hopeful and have a plan in place to manage your siblings' demands and prioritize your mom's care. Remember, it's essential to be patient with yourself and recognize that this is a process. It's also crucial to maintain open communication with your family members and seek additional support when needed. You're not alone in this journey, and I'll be here to offer guidance and support as you navigate the challenges of caregiving.</td>\n",
              "    </tr>\n",
              "    <tr>\n",
              "      <th>6</th>\n",
              "      <td>You are a helpful mental health counselling assistant, please answer the mental health questions based on the patient's description. \\nThe assistant gives helpful, comprehensive, and appropriate answers to the user's questions.</td>\n",
              "      <td>I've been feeling overwhelmed by my responsibilities at work and caring for my aging parents. I've reached a point where I don't know what else I can do, and I'm struggling to communicate this to my boss and family members. I feel guilty for even considering saying no, but I know I need to take care of myself.</td>\n",
              "      <td>I can see how challenging this must be for you. Your situation is complex, and it's understandable that you're feeling overwhelmed. It's important to remember that taking care of yourself is not a selfish act, but rather an essential one for maintaining your overall well-being.\\n\\nAs we work on setting goals, let's focus on creating a balance between your professional and personal life. We can start by identifying your strengths and limitations, and then work on developing a clear and effective communication strategy. This will help you articulate your needs to your boss and family members, allowing you to set healthy boundaries.\\n\\nAdditionally, we can explore the root causes of your guilt feelings when considering saying no. It's common for individuals in caregiving roles to feel a strong sense of obligation, but it's crucial to remember that you're not alone in this situation. We can work on challenging these thoughts and developing a more balanced perspective on self-care and guilt.\\n\\nThrough this process, we'll be employing various counseling techniques, such as cognitive-behavioral therapy and mindfulness practices, to help you manage your emotions and develop a more adaptive response to your situation. By focusing on your strengths, setting clear boundaries, and addressing your guilt feelings, we can help you find a more balanced and fulfilling approach to your responsibilities.\\n\\nTo address these challenges, we can explore several strategies. First, let's work on developing a clear understanding of your personal values and priorities. This will help you determine which requests for help align with your goals and which ones do not. Second, we can practice setting and communicating boundaries, using \"I\" statements to express your feelings and needs. Third, we can identify and challenge any guilt feelings or beliefs that prevent you from prioritizing your own needs. Fourth, we can explore time management techniques, such as scheduling self-care activities and setting realistic expectations for your availability.</td>\n",
              "    </tr>\n",
              "    <tr>\n",
