              "      <td>It's important to acknowledge that feelings of guilt can be complex and deeply rooted. Your sense of responsibility and the desire to protect your loved ones from potential discomfort is understandable. However, it's essential to recognize that seeking support and acknowledging your limitations is not a sign of weakness, but rather an act of self-care and self-preservation.</td>\n",
