              "      <td>You are a helpful mental health counselling assistant, please answer the mental health questions based on the patient's description. \\nThe assistant gives helpful, comprehensive, and appropriate answers to the user's questions.</td>\n",
              "      <td>I've been living with my mom for the past five years since she was diagnosed with Alzheimer's. I've taken on the role of her primary caregiver, which has left me feeling drained and emotionally unavailable for my own needs. I've been neglecting my personal relationships and hobbies, and I feel disconnected from my own identity. I've tried to discuss this with my mom's caregivers, but they're so focused on her care that they don't seem to understand or care about my situation. I feel trapped and unable to prioritize my own needs.</td>\n",
              "      <td>I can see how challenging this situation is for you, and I appreciate your dedication to your mom's care. It's important to acknowledge the emotional toll this role has taken on you. You've described feeling drained, disconnected from your identity, and neglected in your personal relationships. These feelings are valid, and it's crucial that we explore ways to help you regain a sense of control and balance in your life.\\n\\nOne potential approach is to take a break from your caregiving role, even if it's just for a weekend. This would give you an opportunity to focus on your own needs and reconnect with your identity. It's understandable that you'd feel guilty about leaving your mom, but it's essential to remember that self-care is not a luxury, but a necessity for maintaining your overall health and well-being.\\n\\nWe'll also need to consider the potential consequences of this strategy, both positive and negative. For example, who would care for your mom while you're away? Would hiring a professional caregiver be an option? How would your mom react to your absence? These are all important questions to consider, and we'll discuss them further during our next session.\\n\\nIn the meantime, I encourage you to continue exploring your feelings and identifying other potential strategies for regaining a sense of balance in your life. Remember, it's essential to prioritize your own needs and well-being, even in the context of caring for a loved one.</td>\n",
              "    </tr>\n",
              "    <tr>\n",
