              "      <td>I can only imagine how challenging it must be for you to juggle your mom's care, your personal life, and your career. It's a common struggle for caregivers, and it's essential to acknowledge the complexity of your situation. The emotional and physical demands of caregiving can be overwhelming, and it's crucial to prioritize self-care to maintain your well-being.\\n\\nWe can explore various strategies to help you manage your responsibilities more effectively. This may include setting realistic expectations for yourself, delegating tasks, seeking out additional resources, and practicing stress management techniques. It's also essential to recognize the importance of asking for help and accepting support from others.\\n\\nIn our sessions, we can work together to identify specific strategies that will work best for your unique situation. We'll explore the various emotions and challenges that come with caregiving, and I'll provide you with the tools and resources you need to navigate this journey. Remember, it's okay to ask for help, and I'm here to support you every step of the way.</td>\n",
