            "application/vnd.google.colaboratory.intrinsic+json": {
              "type": "dataframe",
              "variable_name": "df2",
              "summary": "{\n  \"name\": \"df2\",\n  \"rows\": 16084,\n  \"fields\": [\n    {\n      \"column\": \"instruction\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"category\",\n        \"num_unique_values\": 1,\n        \"samples\": [\n          \"You are a helpful mental health counselling assistant, please answer the mental health questions based on the patient's description. \\nThe assistant gives helpful, comprehensive, and appropriate answers to the user's questions. \"\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"input\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"string\",\n        \"num_unique_values\": 15856,\n        \"samples\": [\n          \"Good day! Thank you for meeting with me today. I'm here seeking counseling because my anxiety has been significantly impacting my life and preventing me from living it fully. In this session, I hope to understand the root causes of my anxiety and develop effective coping mechanisms.\\n\\nFor quite some time now, I've been experiencing a constant sense of unease. My thoughts are consumed by worries and worst-case scenarios, causing me significant distress. I often feel restless, unable to relax, and struggle to concentrate on tasks or enjoy activities.\\n\\nA recent event that triggered intense anxiety was when I had to attend a social gathering where I did not know many people. Just the thought of interacting with strangers made me extremely anxious. During the gathering, my heart raced, I began sweating profusely, and I felt light-headed.\\n\\nThese symptoms have been present for several months now and occur frequently throughout the week. The intensity varies, but there are days when my anxiety completely immobilizes me, preventing me from leaving the house or engaging in social interactions.\\n\\nReflecting on my past, I recall having a highly critical parent who exerted significant pressure on me to meet high standards. This environment may have contributed to my development of generalized anxiety disorder.\\n\\nCurrently, I utilize deep breathing exercises, grounding techniques, and positive self-talk as coping strategies. While they provide temporary relief, I find it challenging to apply them consistently and effectively.\\n\\nI wanted to discuss potential treatment options available for managing my anxiety. Can you explain how therapy can help in changing negative thinking patterns associated with anxiety? Additionally, are there any alternative therapies you would recommend?\"\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"output\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"string\",\n        \"num_unique_values\": 15984,\n        \"samples\": [\n          \"Navigating challenges related to discrimination and finding acceptance among family and friends can indeed be difficult, as it takes a toll on your mental health. It's commendable that you are seeking coping strategies to help you overcome these obstacles and gain confidence in embracing your LGBTQ identity. \\n\\nOne helpful strategy is to surround yourself with individuals who are supportive and understanding of your identity. Seek out online or in-person communities where you can connect with others who share similar experiences. Engaging with these communities can provide a sense of belonging and support, which can positively impact your mental well-being.\\n\\nEducate yourself about LGBTQ history, rights, and achievements. Understanding the struggles faced by others in the community and their resilience can offer inspiration and strength. Additionally, being knowledgeable about legal protections and resources available to LGBTQ individuals can empower you when advocating for your own rights.\\n\\nSelf-care practices are vital in maintaining good mental health. Find activities that bring you joy, relaxation, or peace, whether it's reading, exercising, crafting, or spending time in nature. Making self-care a priority will replenish your energy, reduce stress, and improve your ability to cope with challenges.\\n\\nConsider seeking professional counseling or therapy. A mental health professional can provide personalized guidance and support tailored to your specific needs. They can also teach you effective coping skills, such as cognitive-behavioral techniques, mindfulness exercises, and stress management strategies. Remember, there are therapists who specialize in working with LGBTQ clients and can offer a safe space free from judgment.\\n\\nAdvocacy can be empowering and therapeutic. Explore opportunities to get involved within the LGBTQ community, whether through volunteering, supporting queer organizations, or attending events and workshops. Contributing to causes you care about can give you a sense of purpose, create a wider support network, and empower you to make a positive impact.\\n\\nFinally, remember that self-acceptance is a journey. Embracing your LGBTQ identity may take time, but know that your identity is valid and deserving of love and acceptance. Surround yourself with affirmations, positive messaging, and supportive resources to remind yourself of this truth.\\n\\nAs you navigate these challenges, believe in yourself and your ability to overcome them. Building a strong support system, practicing self-care, seeking professional guidance when needed, engaging in advocacy, and embracing self-acceptance are important steps toward finding confidence and navigating the discrimination you face. Take things at your own pace and remember that healing and growth are possible.\"\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            }
