              "type": "dataframe",
              "variable_name": "df5",
              "summary": "{\n  \"name\": \"df5\",\n  \"rows\": 13910,\n  \"fields\": [\n    {\n      \"column\": \"label\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"number\",\n        \"std\": 0,\n        \"min\": 0,\n        \"max\": 1,\n        \"num_unique_values\": 2,\n        \"samples\": [\n          0,\n          1\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"input\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"string\",\n        \"num_unique_values\": 13910,\n        \"samples\": [\n          \"AITA for tell my boyfriend to \\\"STFU\\\" during a monopoly game? | As the title says, it didn't end well after a monopoly party. I was winning and was so excited thinking about how to take advantage of the situation. Apparently my boyfriend was suggesting a move (he had already lost) but i was so focused on tge game i told him to \\\"shut the fuck up\\\" twice, i dont even remember that. After our friends left he told me he was upset about what i said. I said it was a game and everything i said or did means nothing outside the game. He wanted me to apologize but I said he was childish for taking things seriously. He won't talk to me now. Help reddit, am I the asshole?\\n\\nTl;dr: i told my vf to shut the fuck up during a monopoly game abd now he wants me to apologize\\n\\nEdit: thank you for opening my eyes. I am the asshole, i should have apologized immediately. After we cooled down i apologized and we're back to normal.\",\n          \"AITA for telling my bf I\\u2019m worried about how much he drinks? | Just wanting a little insight on something that happend recently.\\n\\nMy bfand I had not had a fight until this past weekend and I still feel a little weird about it. We both still live at home so most weekends we sleep at each others\\u2019 place, more often than not my house. Each time my bf comes over he brings 4-6 beers and sometimes a bottle of wine or cider as well.\\n\\nIt didn\\u2019t bother me at first but recently I\\u2019ve started to notice some things. Note that I don\\u2019t drink alcohol, so I don\\u2019t really know much about what is considered normal when it comes to drinking habits.\\n\\nLast weekend he stayed over, we planed on going to dinner with my parents and he took a shower before he left but he took a cider in the shower with him. He even told my parents he was taking a cider into the shower with him because he likes to drink something cold when he\\u2019s having a hot shower. Again I don\\u2019t drink so I don\\u2019t know if this is a normal thing people who drink do. Before we left he had 3 drinks and 2 at dinner. \\n\\nAfter his 2 drinks there he had his head in his hand and tried to stay awake. We asked him to take a break from beer and have water which he did, but would have sips of my mother\\u2019s drink. Not ask her, but would look at her and slowly slide her drink towards him without verbally asking if he could have a sip.\\n\\nWe came home around 10:30 pm and by this time he sobered up a bit and grabbed his last cider in the fridge. I asked him if he thinks he should have another one since we were all going to bed soon and he already had 5 drinks. He snapped at me in front of my mother, I told him to have the cider if he wanted and we both went to my room. He did drink it later.\\n\\nWe talked about what happened right away and I told him that I didn\\u2019t like him snapping at me. He said he was sorry but he doesn\\u2019t like it when people tell him what he can and can\\u2019t do. I told him I wasn\\u2019t trying to tell him what to do but I was concerned with how much I\\u2019ve seen him drink; kind of like how he\\u2019s concerned about me and my eating habits (I don\\u2019t have the best eating habits which he did criticize me about the day before, I am aware of it and it\\u2019s something I am working on improving).\\n\\nI asked him to honestly tell me how much he drinks a week and he said he has about 3 drinks a day on days he\\u2019s not working (about 3-4 days a week) and that the reason he drinks more when he\\u2019s around me is because he feels relaxed around me and he likes to drink when he\\u2019s relaxed. He then went on to explain how many standard drinks are in what he has and says it\\u2019s mostly out of his system within the hour so he can handle alcohol more than I think.\\n\\nUltimately he told me he knows how much he can handle and that night he was fine and I shouldn\\u2019t have to worried like I did. I said okay and we have seemed to move past it but it\\u2019s still worrying me. As I said I don\\u2019t know what\\u2019s considered normal when it comes to drinking, so AITA for telling my boyfriend I\\u2019m worried about how much he drinks?\"\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"is_short\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"boolean\",\n        \"num_unique_values\": 1,\n        \"samples\": [\n          true\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"edited\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"boolean\",\n        \"num_unique_values\": 1,\n        \"samples\": [\n          true\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"
